\section{Stable semistar operations and localizing systems}\label{sect:stable}


A semistar operation $\star$ defined on an integral domain $D$ is called \emph{stable} provided that, for any $E,H\in {\boldsymbol{\overline{F}}}(D)$, we have $(E\cap H)^\star=E^\star\cap H^\star$. We denote by ${\overline{\mbox{\rm\texttt{SStar}}}}(D)$ the set of stable semistar operations on $D$.


