Let $D$ be an integral domain and let $\iota:{\mbox{\rm\texttt{Overr}}}(D)\longrightarrow{\mbox{\rm\texttt{SStar}}_{\!\mbox{\tiny\it\texttt{f}}}}(D)$ be the topological embedding defined in Proposition \ref{immersione}. If $T\in{\mbox{\rm\texttt{Overr}}}(D)$, then $\iota(T)\in{\overline{\mbox{\rm\texttt{SStar}}}}(D)$ if and only if $T$ is flat over $D$.
