It is enough to note that the equality $(I\cap J)T=IT\cap JT$ holds for every ideal $I,J$ of $D$ if and only if $T$ is flat (\cite[Proposition 1.7]{uda} and \cite[Theorem 7.4(i)]{matsu-86}).
